                <h2 id="a1">1. What is a Natural Latex mattress?</h2>
                <p>Natural latex mattresses are a popular kind of mattress for those looking for a bouncy, resilient surface for their comfort. They’re also a popular choice for eco-conscious shoppers, as the material is sustainably sourced from rubber trees.</p>
    
                <h2 id="a2">2. What’s Natural Latex?</h2>
                <p>Natural latex is a material sourced from rubber trees, usually found in tropical regions. The trees are tapped for their rubber polymer sap, which is then mixed with a small amount of organic compounds to reach a gel-like state, then poured into a mold where it takes its shape. </p>
                <p><img src="{{'naturallatex-tree.jpg'|asset_url}}" alt="Natural Latex Tree"></p>
                <p>There are two different processes that are typically used: Talalay and Dunlop. The Talalay process freezes the mixture to preserve consistency while it’s settling, and the Dunlop process does not. </p>
                <p>Not all latex is natural, so make sure the product you’re buying is certified. Synthetic latex is a cheaper material chosen by many brands. It can also be made with the Talalay and Dunlop processes, but it starts with completely manmade rubbers and synthetic materials, sometimes mixed with a small amount of natural rubber tree sap. Synthetic latex doesn’t last as long as natural latex does, and it easily becomes flattened under the weight of frequent use. Synthetic latex is also known for its off-gassing, which can be smelly and even irritate users with allergies. </p>
                
                <p style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><strong>Natural Latex Bedding:</strong></p>
                <ul class="list-group bullets">
                    <li class="list-group-item">No harmful chemicals</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">Can last for around 25 years</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">Low VOCs</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">No strong odor</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><strong>Synthetic Latex Bedding</strong></p>
                <ul class="list-group bullets">
                    <li class="list-group-item">Typically lasts less than 10 years</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">High VOCs</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">Has a strong and smelly odor</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">Can irritate users with allergies</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2 id="a3">3. How is it beneficial for my sleep?</h2>
                <p>Natural latex is soft but supportive, making it a popular choice for use in mattresses, pillows, toppers, crib mattresses, and other bedding. It has high elasticity, providing a “bounce back” feeling and pushing back on the parts of your body that push down harder while you sleep. Natural latex provides an uplifting type of support, relieving sensitive pressure points and responding to all of your movements through the night. This counter pressure makes natural latex a great choice for those with active lifestyles, and those lookings for that “get up and go” morning feeling.</p>
                <p><img src="{{'materials_latex.jpg'|asset_url}}" alt="Natural Latex"></p>
                <p>It’s also a very healthy and breathable material, allowing for increased airflow that keeps you cool through the night. It has hypo-allergenic and antimicrobial properties, resisting mold and dust mites. It’s ideal for those with allergies or who are sensitive to smell.</p>
